sentences: Jerry Hansen was born at Asante Bekwai on 23 February 1927 to Maami Senkire and Johney Hansen, a pharmacist.
In 1939 Hansen left Bekwai to continue his early education at the Methodist School in Koforidua.
He later joined the Accra Academy where he completed his secondary education after obtaining his Oxford and Cambridge certificates in 1947.
On his return to Ghana, Hansen's interest in music made him join the Accra Ochestra in 1949.
To learn how to read the musical score, he joined the city ochestra in the 1950s.
He returned to the Accra Ochestra in 1951 after learning to read the musical score.
Amongst the members of the Accra Ochestra he had met when he joined the group in 1949, Saka Acquaye was the only old member left and there was no one to play the trumpet and trombone.
King Bruce and Saka Acquaye formed a band known as the Black Beats in 1952 and convinced Jerry Hansen to join it.
Hansen played for the Black Beats from 1952 until 1961.
Hansen played for the Black Beats from 1952 until 1961.
In 1961 he founded; the Ramblers International Band with Eddie Owoo, Frank Coffie, Kwesi Forson, Aryee Hammond and a few others (nine in total).

In 1962, the band recorded under Decca's record label releasing singles and LPs, some of which include; "Eka Wonko A", "Saana Owu Bo Fie", "Murusu Maye Den", "Abonsam Fireman", "Oburoni Woewu", "Antie Christie", "Oyi Edze", "Owu Nnye" and "Kae Dabi", "Ponko Abodam".
In 1963, the band continued with hits such as; "Kosor Kopor", "Mitee Momo", "Nyimpa Dasenyi", "Work And Happiness", "Womma Wonka", "Wegya Saman" and "Ewuraba Artificial", "Obra Rehwem".
Nana Ampadu joined the band briefly in 1964.
In 1965 Hansen gained a government scholarship to study Photo and Forensic Laboratory management at Czechoslovakia.
In 1967 the band released two compilations; Dance with the Ramblers and Dance with the Ramblers (LP, Comp) under Decca record label.
In 1971, the band released an album entitled; Doin' Our Own Thing.
In 1974, Hansen helped found the Musicians Union of Ghana (MUSIGA) and was elected president of the union.
In 1976 and 1977 the band released albums; Ramblers International and Ramblers International (LP) respectively.
He received an award at the maiden Music of Ghanaian Origin Dinner and Awards night in 2011, for his contribution to live band music in Ghana.
Hansen died on Saturday morning 7 April 2012 at the Korle Bu Teaching Hospital after battling an ailment.
In Germany, Hansen met the Ramblers; the Netherlands based orchestra which performed in the German city of Stuttgart in the 1950s and 1960s.

sentences: John William Hansen (23 February 1927 – 7 April 2012) popularly known as Jerry Hansen was a Ghanaian highlife musician.
He had his early education at Seventh Day Adventist (SDA) School at Bekwai, where he was first exposed to music.
After two years of working with UAC, Hansen was offered a scholarship to train as an optical mechanic, specializing in the maintenance of cameras and microscopes among others in Germany.

That same year the band was sponsored by the Ghana Union of Great Britain and Ireland to embark on a six-week tour of the United Kingdom.
They toured Czechoslovakia that same year.
The deteriorating economic situation of the country in the early 1980s made it impossible for the band to continue.
Hansen left for the United States of America where he spent most of his later years.
